  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dca, \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0db1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc2\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0da0\u0dca\u0da1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Belarus in nuclear talks with Russia",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko emphasizes that the idea of \u200b\u200bgetting back nuclear weapons to Belarus was caused by Poland's willingness to deploy nuclear weapons from the United States on its territory.",
        "\"The topic came up with the president of Russia after the Poles turned to the Americans and asked them to bring nuclear weapons to Poland. Then I said to President Putin, 'Why are we pretending that nothing is happening?'\" Lukashenko said in his Independence Day speech in the nation's capital, Minsk. said.",
        "On June 25, Lukashenko asked Russian leader Putin to help Belarus adapt to Su-35 aircraft capable of carrying nuclear warheads.",
        "Accordingly, Putin gave the green light to modernize these warplanes and promised that Russia would send tactical missile systems to its ally in the coming months."
      ],
